# Distributed Agent Mesh (DAM)

ğŸš€ **A revolutionary framework for autonomous agents that collaborate via P2P communication**

[![Python 3.8+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.8+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

## ğŸ¯ What is DAM?

Distributed Agent Mesh (DAM) is a **peer-to-peer framework** where autonomous AI agents:
- ğŸ¤– **Decide autonomously** if they can contribute to tasks
- ğŸ¤ **Self-organize** into teams without central control
- âš¡ **Execute in parallel** for maximum performance
- ğŸ”„ **Collaborate directly** via P2P communication
- ğŸ“ˆ **Scale dynamically** by adding/removing agents anytime
- ğŸ’ª **Tolerate failures** - system continues if agents fail

## ğŸ†š DAM vs MCP (Model Context Protocol)

### Architecture Comparison

| Aspect | MCP | DAM |
|--------|-----|-----|
| **Architecture** | Client-Server | P2P Mesh |
| **Control** | Centralized (LLM) | Distributed (Agents) |
| **Decision Making** | LLM decides everything | Agents decide autonomously |
| **Execution** | Sequential tool calls | Parallel agent collaboration |
| **Scalability** | Limited by LLM | Add agents anytime |
| **Resilience** | Single point of failure | Fault tolerant |
| **Performance** | Sequential (1x baseline) | **2-5x faster** (parallel) |

### When to Use What?

**Use MCP when:**
- âœ… Simple tool integration
- âœ… Single-agent systems
- âœ… Well-defined sequential workflows
- âœ… Resource access (files, databases)

**Use DAM when:**
- âœ… Complex, multi-step tasks
- âœ… Tasks requiring parallelism
- âœ… Large-scale distributed systems
- âœ… Systems requiring high availability
- âœ… Dynamic, adaptive workflows

**ğŸ’¡ Best Approach: Hybrid**
- Use MCP for resource access (data, tools)
- Use DAM for agent coordination
- Get the best of both worlds!

